  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Subjects with Obstructive Sleep Apnea (OSA) are at increased risk of developing
      cardiometabolic complications, and effective long-term nCPAP treatment significantly reduces
      the risk of cardiovascular morbidity and mortality.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      1. Primary outcome:

           Incidence of cardiometabolic diseases in subjects with OSA over 9 years.

        2. Secondary outcomes:

      Effects of CPAP treatment on cardiometabolic conditions
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
